{
  "local_port": 40284,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some recipes using 4 ounces of steak?",
  "response": "Here are a few quick and flavorful recipes that incorporate 4 ounces of steak:\n\n### 1. **Steak Tacos**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (flank or sirloin)\n- 2 small corn or flour tortillas\n- 1/4 cup diced onion\n- 1/4 cup chopped cilantro\n- 1 lime (cut into wedges)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Optional: diced avocado or salsa\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Season the steak with salt and pepper.\n2. In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook the steak for about 3-4 minutes per side for medium-rare. Remove and let rest before slicing thinly.\n3. Warm the tortillas in the same skillet for a minute on each side.\n4. Assemble the tacos by placing steak on the tortillas, then topping with diced onion, cilantro, and optional toppings.\n5. Squeeze lime over the tacos and serve.\n\n### 2. **Steak Salad**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (ribeye or sirloin)\n- Mixed salad greens (spinach, arugula, or lettuce)\n- 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/4 cucumber, sliced\n- 1/4 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 2 tbsp vinaigrette dressing\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Season the steak with salt and pepper.\n2. Grill or sear the steak in a skillet for 3-4 minutes on each side for medium-rare. Let it rest, then slice thinly.\n3. In a large bowl, combine salad greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, and red onion.\n4. Add the sliced steak on top and drizzle with vinaigrette. Toss gently and serve.\n\n### 3. **Steak Stir-Fry**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz flank steak, thinly sliced against the grain\n- 1 cup mixed bell peppers, sliced\n- 1/2 cup broccoli florets\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 inch ginger, minced\n- 2 tbsp soy sauce\n- 1 tsp sesame oil\n- Cooked rice or noodles, for serving\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Heat sesame oil in a pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and ginger, saut\u00e9 for about 30 seconds.\n2. Add the sliced steak and cook until browned (about 2-3 minutes).\n3. Toss in the mixed bell peppers and broccoli, cooking for another 3-4 minutes until the vegetables are tender.\n4. Drizzle with soy sauce, stir well and serve over cooked rice or noodles.\n\n### 4. **Steak and Eggs**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (any cut)\n- 2 eggs\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- Optional: fresh herbs (like parsley or chives) for garnish\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Season the steak with salt and pepper.\n2. In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat and cook the steak for about 3-4 minutes per side, depending on the desired doneness. Remove and let rest.\n3. In the same skillet, crack in the eggs and cook to your liking (sunny-side up, scrambled, etc.).\n4. Slice the steak and serve alongside the eggs, garnishing with fresh herbs if desired.\n\nThese recipes make good use of 4 ounces of steak while providing variety and satisfying meals. Enjoy!",
